137
00:08:04,450 --> 00:08:08,030
Well, for me...

138
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:13,740
I won't allow that! I won't allow that!

139
00:08:15,510 --> 00:08:18,150
What about Akamine?

140
00:08:18,150 --> 00:08:20,070
What? Why her?

141
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:23,600
That's because...

142
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:26,090
Previously, I couldn't greet her properly.

143
00:08:26,090 --> 00:08:28,900
- She's my...
- I'm Reina Akamine.

144
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:32,040
I'm from the HR department. I entered the company together with Yamamoto.

145
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:34,170
Please excuse me.

146
00:08:34,170 --> 00:08:37,160
But if she comes along, it will be problematic...

147
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:39,130
For your invitation,

148
00:08:41,170 --> 00:08:43,790
I'm most happy to accept it.

149
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:45,800
Akamine.

150
00:08:50,790 --> 00:08:52,380
Don't you only drink wine?

151
00:08:52,380 --> 00:08:56,670
Did I ever say something like that?

152
00:08:59,180 --> 00:09:01,250
Sorry to keep you waiting.

153
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:04,240
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

154
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:07,360
This looks so delicious.

155
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,750
Let's cheers.

156
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:12,100
Cheers!

157
00:09:19,250 --> 00:09:21,810
So, Yamamoto and Akamine entered the company at the same time?

158
00:09:21,810 --> 00:09:23,470
Yes, that's right.

159
00:09:23,470 --> 00:09:27,210
During the freshman training, we were in the same group and got along well at once.

160
00:09:27,210 --> 00:09:32,070
What do you mean by getting along well? I was the one who did all the work.

161
00:09:32,070 --> 00:09:34,950
Didn't you do them because you liked it?

162
00:09:34,950 --> 00:09:37,930
Didn't you cry at the end of the training because you couldn't bear to part with it?

163
00:09:37,930 --> 00:09:41,620
I cried because I was finally able to get away from you.

164
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:43,190
Don't say that.

165
00:09:43,190 --> 00:09:45,430
Hayami, what would you like to drink next?

166
00:09:45,430 --> 00:09:47,580
Let me see.

167
00:09:47,580 --> 00:09:50,860
- How about this?
- I was also thinking of the same thing.

168
00:09:50,860 --> 00:09:54,120
Local craft beer is always interesting.

169
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,870
There is a brewery at Yakushima in Kyushu,

170
00:09:56,870 --> 00:10:00,000
and they have a citrusy pale ale.

171
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,920
I know that! I've been thinking of drinking it, but it's always sold out.

172
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:07,220
If that's the case, I'll get some for you when I return to Fukuoka.

173
00:10:07,220 --> 00:10:08,920
- Would that be fine?
- Yes.

174
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:10,500
Yeah.

175
00:10:12,940 --> 00:10:16,910
Both of you looks so compatible together!

176
00:10:16,910 --> 00:10:21,280
- What?
- You like the same beer, and you drink at the same pace.

177
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:24,020
It would be fun if both of you are together!

178
00:10:24,020 --> 00:10:26,050
You don't need to care about us here.

179
00:10:26,050 --> 00:10:29,410
And both of you are the aces of the sales department!

180
00:10:29,410 --> 00:10:31,690
You must have a lot in common.

181
00:10:31,690 --> 00:10:34,580
- Akamine, what are you...
- Yamamoto.

182
00:10:34,580 --> 00:10:39,090
I would like to have chorizo edamame, fish and chips, shrimp ajillo for finger food.

183
00:10:39,090 --> 00:10:40,790
Huh?

184
00:10:40,790 --> 00:10:42,690
I said...

185
00:10:42,690 --> 00:10:47,180
chorizo edamame, fish and chips, shrimp ajillo!

186
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:51,780
- You want me to get them? Why me?
- Chorizo edamame, fish and chips, shrimp ajillo!

187
00:10:51,780 --> 00:10:55,670
I've already memorized them!

188
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:57,190
Yamamoto, you are such a kind person.

189
00:10:57,190 --> 00:11:00,030
If I don't do it, she's bound to continue saying it for life.

190
00:11:00,030 --> 00:11:02,390
Well, this is the result of my education.

191
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:04,110
Stop it.

192
00:11:07,620 --> 00:11:09,150
Can I have the finger food platter?

193
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:12,610
No problem. Please wait for a while.

194
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:19,650
What is that Akamine thinking about?

195
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,820
Let me help you.

196
00:11:22,820 --> 00:11:26,090
- You can't carry everything alone, right?
- Koga, you're here.

197
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:30,080
I feel sorry.

198
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,550
Eh?

199
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:35,410
You must have wanted to come here with only Hayami.

200
00:11:35,410 --> 00:11:37,750
That's not true.

201
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,940
It's just the problem with Akamine.

202
00:11:39,940 --> 00:11:43,730
Hayami also seems to be having fun with you.

203
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,600
Is it?

204
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:01,210
Are you okay? Are you not feeling well?

205
00:12:01,210 --> 00:12:02,550
What?

206
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:08,180
Are you living together with Yamamoto?

207
00:12:08,180 --> 00:12:09,900
Why do you---?

208
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,980
That's right. You are with the human resource department.

209
00:12:14,980 --> 00:12:17,640
Why Yamamoto?

210
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:19,500
That's because...

211
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:21,490
he might look pleasant at first impression,

212
00:12:21,490 --> 00:12:24,960
but he's a calculative and stingy fellow.

213
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:28,590
Do you know that?

214
00:12:28,590 --> 00:12:33,220
He got dumped by this ex-girlfriend because she said she didn't need two "mothers"!

215
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:35,630
Really?

216
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:40,200
Isn't there nothing good about living with him?

217
00:12:41,930 --> 00:12:44,870
I can only think of the good things.

218
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:46,820
Eh?

219
00:12:46,820 --> 00:12:48,500
In the beginning,

220
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:52,910
I was a little shocked by how over-concerned he can get over things,

221
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:55,100
but I think that's because...

222
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:58,870
