261
00:15:37,190 --> 00:15:38,880
Do you think so?

262
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:42,420
It's you whose face is getting red.

263
00:15:43,060 --> 00:15:47,670
My blood circulation is good today.

264
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:52,520
This is not going to end, since both of us don't want to lose.

265
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,390
That's true.

266
00:15:55,570 --> 00:15:58,060
But it's just like what she said.

267
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:00,870
We drink at the same pace.

268
00:16:00,870 --> 00:16:02,190
That's right.

269
00:16:02,190 --> 00:16:07,060
Maybe we should try out to see how compatible we are.

270
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:10,590
Do you want to try it out?

271
00:16:10,590 --> 00:16:14,390
What? Are you still going to drink?

272
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:16,360
Put down your glass for a moment.

273
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:19,170
Put it down.

274
00:16:24,930 --> 00:16:28,750
Even if it's just a trial, I'm going all out.

275
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:30,920
Don't try to escape.

276
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:58,540
Why isn't she picking up the call?

277
00:16:58,540 --> 00:17:00,820
Both of you are compatible!

278
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:03,340
They look like an ideal couple.

279
00:17:03,340 --> 00:17:04,710
What do you think of Koga?

280
00:17:04,710 --> 00:17:08,470
He has a unique charisma.

281
00:17:08,470 --> 00:17:11,450
No way! It can't be!

282
00:17:11,450 --> 00:17:14,420
To make someone cling to you

283
00:17:14,420 --> 00:17:17,440
and want you more!

284
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:21,460
And then you make your move...

285
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:23,060
and eat her up!

286
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:01,670
Get ready...

287
00:18:01,670 --> 00:18:03,850
- What?
- This way!

288
00:18:05,490 --> 00:18:10,630
I've failed 30 times consecutively. We aren't compatible at all.

289
00:18:10,630 --> 00:18:12,840
There's no way...

290
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:16,140
So, they are just playing a game.

291
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,880
Eh? It's Yamamoto.

292
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:21,790
Yes, it's me.

293
00:18:21,790 --> 00:18:25,440
Did you see that I won just now? I think Koga is already drunk.

294
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:28,070
You look drunk yourself, too.

295
00:18:28,070 --> 00:18:32,280
I'm not drunk. If I'm drunk, I would be singing R&B now.

296
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:34,090
What is that?

297
00:18:34,090 --> 00:18:37,210
Okay, let's go home now. Koga, you too.

298
00:18:37,210 --> 00:18:40,520
I'm still going to drink. You can take Hayami back first.

299
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:41,900
What?

300
00:18:44,070 --> 00:18:49,440
I feel bad if I don't leave you both alone to yourselves.

301
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:52,350
What are you talking about?

302
00:18:52,350 --> 00:18:55,190
Let's go back. Quick, get your own bag.

303
00:18:55,190 --> 00:18:56,580
Okay.

304
00:18:56,580 --> 00:18:58,990
- Where's my bag?
- Here.

305
00:18:58,990 --> 00:19:00,790
Okay.

306
00:19:00,790 --> 00:19:04,970
Then we shall take our leave.

307
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:18,380
I'm not drunk. If I'm drunk, I'll make sure that I win.

308
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:20,990
This is the first time I've seen you so drunk.

309
00:19:20,990 --> 00:19:23,080
I told you that I'm not drunk!

310
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:27,120
Looks that you were having fun with Koga just now.

311
00:19:27,950 --> 00:19:31,810
You must have had fun with Akamine, too!

312
00:19:31,810 --> 00:19:34,830
Eh, what are you talking about?

313
00:19:34,830 --> 00:19:38,860
Well, you have feelings for each other anyway.

314
00:19:38,860 --> 00:19:40,230
Eh?

315
00:19:41,830 --> 00:19:45,260
Who do you mean by having mutual feelings? Akamine and I?

316
00:19:45,260 --> 00:19:47,280
I shouldn't have say it out.

317
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:50,040
Before any clarfications,

318
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:54,300
do you really think that I like Akamine?

319
00:19:55,130 --> 00:19:56,930
Am I wrong?

320
00:19:56,930 --> 00:19:59,830
Huh? Of course not.

321
00:19:59,830 --> 00:20:01,530
Why do you think that way?

322
00:20:01,530 --> 00:20:06,520
That's because you were pinned to the wall the other time.

323
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:11,250
That's just something Akamine is fond of doing. There's nothing else to it.

324
00:20:11,250 --> 00:20:12,980
You don't need to feel shy about it.

325
00:20:12,980 --> 00:20:15,640
I really mean it.

326
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:17,750
I don't like her at all.

327
00:20:23,070 --> 00:20:26,170
Okay, that's great then.

328
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:28,550
Eh?

329
00:20:28,550 --> 00:20:31,290
I was getting a bit worried about it.

330
00:20:31,290 --> 00:20:34,540
Because you both look so close.

331
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:38,200
I say, Hayami.

332
00:20:40,170 --> 00:20:42,660
Since you are talking about it...

333
00:20:43,290 --> 00:20:45,380
Don't tell me...

334
00:20:50,210 --> 00:20:54,090
that you are interested in me?

335
00:20:57,610 --> 00:20:59,290
N-o...

336
00:20:59,290 --> 00:21:03,370
You must be interested in me. That's for sure.

337
00:21:03,370 --> 00:21:06,230
No, I'm not interested in you.

338
00:21:06,230 --> 00:21:09,320
Are you acting weird recently due to this reason?

339
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:11,480
Because you are interested in me.

340
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:14,680
Look, there's a rare species of grass over there!

341
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,450
Hayami.

342
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:20,110
I'm asking you seriously.

343
00:21:27,210 --> 00:21:29,370
Please give me an answer.

344
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:34,910
I'm drunk now, so I can't think properly.

345
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:37,780
You said that you're not drunk.

346
00:21:40,530 --> 00:21:42,910
- But...
- I won't let you go.

347
00:21:44,020 --> 00:21:47,420
No matter what happens today, I won't let you go.

348
00:21:49,450 --> 00:21:51,290
Unless you tell me

349
00:21:52,380 --> 00:21:55,050
how you really feell.

350
00:21:55,860 --> 00:21:59,090
- Hayami, do you like---
- No...

351
00:21:59,090 --> 00:22:01,780
I'm just a little interested in you.

352
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:28,350
See you.

353
00:22:39,750 --> 00:22:43,120
I let the cat out of the bag.

354
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:47,130
No way.

355
00:22:48,150 --> 00:22:49,920
This means...

356
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,370
[Improvement]

357
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:53,170
This is an improvement.

358
00:22:53,170 --> 00:22:56,650
[Masami Yamamoto, Chihiro's eldest brother]

359
00:22:57,520 --> 00:23:00,010
[Kaoru Yamamoto, Chihiro's second brother]
Are you practising calligraphy at this time?

360
00:23:00,010 --> 00:23:04,680
No, I just felt something.

361
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:10,700
[CONTRACT]

362
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:17,690
Yes! That's great!

363
00:23:19,310 --> 00:23:20,860
[CONTRACT]

364
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,400
What should I do?

365
00:23:29,330 --> 00:23:34,450
Good morning. I'm leaving first today, and I don't need dinner tonight.

366
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:40,260
This looks a bit...

367
00:23:40,260 --> 00:23:41,580
You escaped?

368
00:23:41,580 --> 00:23:43,790
That's because...

369
00:23:43,790 --> 00:23:47,630
it looks like I'm just played around by a younger man.

370
00:23:47,630 --> 00:23:51,910
He was giggling to himself all the way home yesterday.

371
00:23:51,910 --> 00:23:57,210
But you've acknowledged your feelings. There's no way for you to turn back now.

372
00:23:57,210 --> 00:24:00,460
No, I can still do it. I can still turn back in time.

373
00:24:00,460 --> 00:24:05,590
Is it really that scary to be torn into pieces by his brother?

374
00:24:06,270 --> 00:24:09,840
That's part of the reason,

375
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:15,950
but if I were to acknowledge my feelings now,

376
00:24:15,950 --> 00:24:18,700
the life that I'm enjoying now will be destroyed.

377
00:24:21,870 --> 00:24:26,690
If I were to have a love relationship with Yamamoto,

378
00:24:26,690 --> 00:24:30,870
it would end someday.

379
00:24:30,870 --> 00:24:33,470
Because he's your important "wife"?

380
00:24:39,130 --> 00:24:40,730
Honoka.

381
00:24:43,180 --> 00:24:47,080
Sorry, but I still don't get it.

382
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:49,280
[RACCOON ELECTRONICS]

383
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:52,340
Do you mean to help in a new product development?

384
00:24:52,340 --> 00:24:55,770
Yes, our refrigerator is going through a renewal,

385
00:24:55,770 --> 00:25:00,350
so the business development department hopes to gather feedback from each department.

386
00:25:00,350 --> 00:25:04,350
I'm thinking that both of you can represent the sales department.

387
00:25:04,350 --> 00:25:06,790
Because both of you are our aces.

388
00:25:08,420 --> 00:25:14,100
But it will add to your current workload, so you will get busier.

389
00:25:14,100 --> 00:25:16,000
Get busier?

390
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:18,530
Is that a no?

391
00:25:18,530 --> 00:25:21,180
- Maybe I should ask someone else.
- No.

392
00:25:21,180 --> 00:25:24,330
I will do it. Please let me do it.

393
00:25:24,330 --> 00:25:26,520
Hayami, that's great.

394
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:28,850
It's settled then.

395
00:25:28,850 --> 00:25:32,240
I've gathered information about the company sales.

396
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:35,540
I thought it would be good to analyse our sales point.

397
00:25:35,540 --> 00:25:39,420
Oh yes. Maybe I should ask someone else to do the research for other companies, too.

398
00:25:39,420 --> 00:25:41,530
Can Ishii help us? Let me go ask him.

399
00:25:41,530 --> 00:25:44,030
- Hayami.
- Yes?

400
00:25:44,030 --> 00:25:46,740
- Please calm down.
- Yes?

401
00:25:48,370 --> 00:25:53,530
Look at the whiteboard where there's nothing written.

402
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:58,530
Okay, take a deep breath.

403
00:26:04,950 --> 00:26:07,820
How do you feel? Have you calmed down?

404
00:26:08,590 --> 00:26:11,520
Yes, a little.

405
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:13,310
Did something happen yesterday?

406
00:26:13,310 --> 00:26:14,350
Eh?

407
00:26:14,350 --> 00:26:19,320
I thought that I was being nosy to let you go back with Yamamoto.

408
00:26:20,580 --> 00:26:23,200
Everything is fine, really.

409
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:24,920
If so, that's good.

410
00:26:26,170 --> 00:26:30,990
But I'm surprised that you remember all the details. I thought you were drunk.

411
00:26:30,990 --> 00:26:32,870
No, I was not drunk.

412
00:26:32,870 --> 00:26:37,640
Eh? But I've not seen you smiling so brightly before.

413
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:41,170
Please forget it. It concerns my authority.

414
00:26:41,170 --> 00:26:42,440
Authority?

415
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:47,290
I think it was great to talk to you.

416
00:26:47,290 --> 00:26:48,750
Really?

417
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:57,930
Yamamoto, don't the both of them look good together?

418
00:26:59,290 --> 00:27:02,480
Why are you grinning like that?

419
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:04,130
I've already decided

420
00:27:04,130 --> 00:27:09,120
not to get all emotional over Hayami's actions.

421
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:11,460
That's because...

422
00:27:11,460 --> 00:27:15,530
she's into...

423
00:27:15,530 --> 00:27:17,710
- What?
- What?

424
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:28,390
Wait, Yamamoto. Finish up what you want to say.

425
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:40,170
Hanazuma.

426
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:45,560
- Did you make this?
- Yes.

427
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:48,990
Due to your previous advice,

428
00:27:48,990 --> 00:27:51,180
I've decided to give it another try.

429
00:27:51,180 --> 00:27:55,110
You don't always have to be cheerful,

430
00:27:55,110 --> 00:28:00,280
so it's fine to feel frustrated sometimes.

431
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:02,660
I see.

432
00:28:02,660 --> 00:28:05,990
But this part is not well-made.

433
00:28:05,990 --> 00:28:10,040
Next time, I'll make it look even better.

434
00:28:15,320 --> 00:28:20,050
I think a frustrated Hanazuma can be good at times, too.

435
00:28:20,050 --> 00:28:22,480
I'll help myself then.

436
00:28:23,430 --> 00:28:25,350
Hayami.

437
00:28:25,350 --> 00:28:29,080
How is it going with the person that you are cohabiting with?

438
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:33,420
Well, I seem to be in a bad situation.

439
00:28:33,420 --> 00:28:37,150
I told him that I'm interested in him.

440
00:28:37,150 --> 00:28:38,880
Just as I expected.

441
00:28:39,750 --> 00:28:43,770
But didn't you say that you wanted to turn back?

442
00:28:43,770 --> 00:28:45,920
Don't worry. I'll turn back from now onwards.

443
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:50,290
I'll bury myself in work and distance away from him.

444
00:28:50,290 --> 00:28:51,660
Then,

445
00:28:52,380 --> 00:28:54,880
I shall support you!

446
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:56,330
Eh?

447
00:28:56,330 --> 00:28:59,950
Good morning. I have morning activities, so I'll leave first.

448
00:28:59,950 --> 00:29:01,380
What?

449
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:04,130
Morning activities?

450
00:29:04,130 --> 00:29:06,800
Here, this is for you.

451
00:29:06,800 --> 00:29:08,520
You don't have to make breakfast.

452
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:11,340
You came early to the office for me,

453
00:29:11,340 --> 00:29:13,710
so please let me do this.

454
00:29:13,710 --> 00:29:17,780
Then, I shall not hesitate further. Thank you.

455
00:29:22,530 --> 00:29:24,350
This is delicious!

456
00:29:26,110 --> 00:29:29,430
Good morning, Yamamoto.

457
00:29:29,430 --> 00:29:31,950
Good morning.

458
00:29:31,950 --> 00:29:33,150
What are you doing?

459
00:29:33,150 --> 00:29:34,880
From today during mornings,

460
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:40,540
Hayami will be teaching me her sales secrets.

461
00:29:40,540 --> 00:29:45,990
You see, we are busy during work time, so we are using the free time in the morning.

462
00:29:45,990 --> 00:29:48,810
- Isn't that right?
- Yes!

463
00:29:48,810 --> 00:29:52,820
I see...

464
00:29:55,510 --> 00:29:58,580
In order to create a new product,

465
00:29:58,580 --> 00:30:01,540
it would be better to have new functions, right?

466
00:30:01,540 --> 00:30:04,280
For example, connecting with an app?

467
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:08,710
For a fridge, is it necessary to have other functions other than keeping things cold?

468
00:30:08,710 --> 00:30:10,450
That's true.

469
00:30:10,450 --> 00:30:13,990
My fridge is used only for cooling my drinks.

470
00:30:13,990 --> 00:30:17,980
I understand, because I used to be like that, too.

471
00:30:17,980 --> 00:30:21,520
Eh? So, you've changed?

472
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:26,550
That's due to... many circumstances.

473
00:30:32,850 --> 00:30:37,360
I think my fridge at home is used for other functions, too.

474
00:30:43,130 --> 00:30:45,480
Why?

475
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:49,620
Are you feeling upset now? Didn't you say you won't get emotional?

476
00:30:49,620 --> 00:30:51,940
I'm not!

477
00:30:51,940 --> 00:30:53,700
Not even a little bit?

478
00:30:53,700 --> 00:30:57,560
I said no! You're annoying.

479
00:30:57,560 --> 00:31:00,910
You called me annoying? I'm still your superior in the office.

480
00:31:06,460 --> 00:31:09,850
Today, I have morning activities, too.

481
00:31:11,980 --> 00:31:13,730
I'm okay.

482
00:31:13,730 --> 00:31:17,670
Because you are interested in me.

483
00:31:17,670 --> 00:31:19,670
She's interested in me.

484
00:31:19,670 --> 00:31:22,150
She's interested in me.

485
00:31:22,150 --> 00:31:26,790
- She's interested...
- Are you talking to yourself?

486
00:31:26,790 --> 00:31:29,180
Akamine.

487
00:31:30,730 --> 00:31:33,360
- Why did you...
- Don't talk about me.

488
00:31:33,360 --> 00:31:36,020
Recently, Hayami and Koga

489
00:31:36,020 --> 00:31:39,750
have been staying late together.

490
00:31:39,750 --> 00:31:41,620
That's due to work.

491
00:31:41,620 --> 00:31:45,760
And in the morning, she's with the cute newcomer.

492
00:31:47,820 --> 00:31:51,990
She might have eyes for other people!

493
00:31:51,990 --> 00:31:55,010
Recently, there are many great guys in the sales department.

494
00:31:55,930 --> 00:31:59,000
By the way, I'm supporting the pair of

495
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:01,420
Koga and Hayami.

496
00:32:08,670 --> 00:32:10,960
I hope that you can be my wife?

497
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:15,070
Did he say that?

498
00:32:19,530 --> 00:32:23,320
Did he say that to you suddenly? The man that you are living with?

499
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:26,590
Yes, that was the reason of our house-sharing.

500
00:32:26,590 --> 00:32:29,410
He cooks really well, too.

501
00:32:29,410 --> 00:32:30,820
That gave me a shock.

502
00:32:30,820 --> 00:32:35,360
I think it was during the golden week.

503
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:38,370
Then, it will soon be a month.

504
00:32:38,370 --> 00:32:40,700
A month?

505
00:32:40,700 --> 00:32:43,600
Time really passes fast.

506
00:32:44,370 --> 00:32:46,840
- Are you sick of it yet?
- What?

507
00:32:47,490 --> 00:32:50,130
You see. Sometimes you just want to be

508
00:32:50,130 --> 00:32:54,160
with a different person or eat different food, right?

509
00:32:54,160 --> 00:32:58,820
If I'm with someone everyday for a month, I think I will get sick of the person.

510
00:33:01,950 --> 00:33:04,510
[Today, I have morning activities, too.]

511
00:33:05,970 --> 00:33:07,590
Okay.

512
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:14,720
Good morning, Yamamoto.

513
00:33:22,980 --> 00:33:24,710
[Lasagne]

514
00:33:26,120 --> 00:33:28,790
[Rocket salad]

515
00:33:28,790 --> 00:33:29,840
[Acqua pazza]

516
00:33:29,840 --> 00:33:31,790
[Gazpacho pasta]
Eh?

517
00:33:33,050 --> 00:33:34,590
What's all these?

518
00:33:36,990 --> 00:33:38,950
[It's a feast tonight!]

519
00:33:38,950 --> 00:33:40,800
Feast?

520
00:33:41,540 --> 00:33:43,190
Therefore...

521
00:33:46,620 --> 00:33:48,260
Okay, I know.

522
00:33:49,890 --> 00:33:51,550
That's good.

523
00:33:57,790 --> 00:33:59,690
What? Are you soaking this in water?

524
00:33:59,690 --> 00:34:03,250
Yes, if you soak dry pasta,

525
00:34:03,250 --> 00:34:07,950
it will become as soft as your cheeks.

526
00:34:09,410 --> 00:34:11,850
But what's gotten into you?

527
00:34:11,850 --> 00:34:14,430
For someone who's good at homecooking like you,

528
00:34:14,430 --> 00:34:17,830
why do you suddenly want to make exquisite Italian food?

529
00:34:17,830 --> 00:34:22,070
Well, I have my reasons.

530
00:34:22,070 --> 00:34:23,790
Don't tell me...

531
00:34:23,790 --> 00:34:27,900
It's because of your beloved Hayami?

532
00:34:27,900 --> 00:34:29,550
Eh?

533
00:34:29,550 --> 00:34:30,680
How do you know?

534
00:34:30,680 --> 00:34:33,150
Because you are my cute brother,

535
00:34:33,150 --> 00:34:37,480
so I-can-see-through-you.

536
00:34:38,780 --> 00:34:41,960
So, how much have you both progressed?

537
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:44,420
Hug? Kiss? Something more than that?

538
00:34:44,420 --> 00:34:47,640
We've not reached that stage yet. Stop it.

539
00:34:47,640 --> 00:34:49,840
That's really slow then.

540
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:53,390
But there's been a slight improvement.

541
00:34:53,390 --> 00:34:57,150
But I would like to grab the opportunity to speed things up.

542
00:34:57,150 --> 00:35:01,040
I see. Through satisfying her stomach, right?

543
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:03,620
Then just leave it to me.

544
00:35:03,620 --> 00:35:08,060
I will create a sticky cheese bath to

545
00:35:08,060 --> 00:35:11,410
bring-you-together!

546
00:35:11,410 --> 00:35:12,880
Cheese bath?

547
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:14,460
Magnet?

548
00:35:14,460 --> 00:35:16,920
Recently, in order to make the design look great,

549
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:20,940
there's an increase of fridges that do not have magnetic doors.

550
00:35:20,940 --> 00:35:25,580
However, from the feedback of the stores, when customers are looking for a replacement,

551
00:35:25,580 --> 00:35:28,810
that causes some problem for them.

552
00:35:28,810 --> 00:35:33,200
In other words, a necessary function for our new fridge is

553
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:35,390
a magnetic door?

554
00:35:35,390 --> 00:35:40,020
Yes, of course it must also have the other basic functions.

555
00:35:40,020 --> 00:35:42,130
But comparing with other brands,

556
00:35:42,130 --> 00:35:46,110
wouldn't it better to have apps to link to the fridge?

557
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:49,600
Apart from a stylish design and new functions,

558
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:53,750
it would better to have a simple design suitable for daily life.

559
00:35:53,750 --> 00:35:57,880
That would create a difference from the other brands.

560
00:35:57,880 --> 00:36:03,130
This is the results gathered from the customers in the city.

561
00:36:03,130 --> 00:36:05,560
I hope it would be good reference.

562
00:36:05,560 --> 00:36:10,060
I see. I'm glad that we got to hear from the sales department.

563
00:36:10,060 --> 00:36:12,610
- We're glad to be of help.
- We're glad to be of help.

564
00:36:12,610 --> 00:36:15,330
I'm glad that they are happy with our presentation.

565
00:36:15,330 --> 00:36:19,950
Well, our work gets easier if the company has a good product.

566
00:36:19,950 --> 00:36:22,580
That's right.

567
00:36:22,580 --> 00:36:26,120
I need to go to the convenience store to get dinner.

568
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:29,180
So, are you going to take videos of your food again today?

569
00:36:30,010 --> 00:36:32,580
If I have the mood.

570
00:36:32,580 --> 00:36:34,810
During the previous health checkup,

571
00:36:34,810 --> 00:36:37,910
the doctor told me to change my diet.

572
00:36:37,910 --> 00:36:39,720
Eh? Are you okay?

573
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:41,860
No problem at all.

574
00:36:41,860 --> 00:36:44,520
What about you? What are you having for dinner today?

575
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:48,910
My dinner? There is lasagne,

576
00:36:48,910 --> 00:36:52,820
rocket salad, acqua pazza,

577
00:36:52,820 --> 00:36:58,280
and something gazpacho, I think.

578
00:36:58,280 --> 00:37:02,160
Sounds great. Which restaurant are you going to?

579
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:05,520
No, it's Yamamoto...

580
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:06,850
What?

581
00:37:07,680 --> 00:37:09,500
Yamamoto?

582
00:37:11,550 --> 00:37:15,320
That's because...

583
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:19,700
Hey, I've been wondering.

584
00:37:19,700 --> 00:37:21,700
Are the two of you...?

585
00:37:37,260 --> 00:37:40,290
Maybe this is too much?

586
00:37:40,290 --> 00:37:42,270
It's fine.

587
00:37:42,270 --> 00:37:45,860
This is for the love of Hayami and Chihiro,

588
00:37:45,860 --> 00:37:50,750
and it needs to be dealt-with-a-blow.

589
00:37:50,750 --> 00:37:52,360
I hope things go well.

590
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:55,230
Then I shall take my leave.

591
00:37:55,230 --> 00:37:56,950
Thank you.

592
00:38:02,350 --> 00:38:03,770
Eh!?

593
00:38:05,500 --> 00:38:07,470
Is something wrong?

594
00:38:10,630 --> 00:38:13,920
Mamma mia!

595
00:38:20,810 --> 00:38:25,550
Sorry, but I told Koga about our house-sharing.

596
00:38:25,550 --> 00:38:28,140
And also about the "wife" and "pillar" of the house.

597
00:38:28,140 --> 00:38:30,920
It seems that the mystery is solved.

598
00:38:30,920 --> 00:38:33,140
I see.

599
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:38,310
But don't worry. I've also told him that we are not in a relationship.

600
00:38:38,310 --> 00:38:40,870
Eh...

601
00:38:40,870 --> 00:38:45,970
So, I was thinking to invite Koga to eat your food,

602
00:38:45,970 --> 00:38:49,400
because you are cooking a feast today.

603
00:38:51,510 --> 00:38:54,310
Please come inside.

604
00:38:55,370 --> 00:38:57,700
It's really a feast!

605
00:38:57,700 --> 00:38:59,590
Wait. Let me take a photo.

606
00:38:59,590 --> 00:39:02,360
Yamamoto, you are really fantastic.

607
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:05,380
Do you make this everyday?

608
00:39:07,010 --> 00:39:11,100
[Happy One Month Anniversary]

609
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:29,160
Hayami, I'm sorry.

610
00:39:29,160 --> 00:39:33,030
I feel a sudden pain in my chest, so I need to go.

611
00:39:33,030 --> 00:39:35,040
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm fine.

612
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:37,200
It's psychogenetic.

613
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:39,680
Yamamoto, see you.

614
00:39:41,370 --> 00:39:42,520
Are you really okay?

615
00:39:42,520 --> 00:39:46,070
- Sorry for disrupting.
- Take care.

616
00:39:48,720 --> 00:39:51,550
Is he really alright?

617
00:39:51,550 --> 00:39:54,790
Are you still thinking about Koga?

618
00:39:54,790 --> 00:39:58,580
Eh?

619
00:39:58,580 --> 00:40:03,640
He might look healthy, but he doesn't eat properly.

620
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:07,110
I wonder if he might just collapse one day.

621
00:40:09,650 --> 00:40:13,450
Then what about Hanazuma?

622
00:40:13,450 --> 00:40:15,600
Hanazuma?

623
00:40:15,600 --> 00:40:17,740
Is there anything that you like about him?

624
00:40:18,540 --> 00:40:21,350
- Why so sudden...
- Is there anything?

625
00:40:21,350 --> 00:40:24,160
Let me think.

626
00:40:25,060 --> 00:40:30,550
Hanazuma may seem like a perfectionist,

627
00:40:30,550 --> 00:40:34,430
but I hope that he won't force himself too hard.

628
00:40:35,420 --> 00:40:37,850
I see.

629
00:40:37,850 --> 00:40:41,240
So, these are the things that you are concerned about.

630
00:40:42,910 --> 00:40:47,940
Wait. Did I just fell into some kind of trap?

631
00:40:47,940 --> 00:40:50,620
No, it's not what you think.

632
00:40:50,620 --> 00:40:52,410
But it's true to say that

633
00:40:52,410 --> 00:40:55,900
there are many people whom you care about in this world.

634
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:57,920
Yamamoto?

635
00:40:57,920 --> 00:41:02,890
Life is filled with uncertainties, so it's best to care about others in your life,

636
00:41:02,890 --> 00:41:07,350
so that you will not be alone,

637
00:41:07,350 --> 00:41:09,590
especially in this era.

638
00:41:09,590 --> 00:41:12,920
I don't know what you are talking about.

639
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:17,550
I'm not the "wife" who belongs to you alone.

640
00:41:19,050 --> 00:41:24,660
- Eh?
- I'm already full from all the tasting, so I'll clear this side away.

641
00:41:26,330 --> 00:41:30,910
Wait. What did you just say?

642
00:41:30,910 --> 00:41:32,520
I just said...

643
00:41:32,520 --> 00:41:38,170
I'm not the "wife" who belongs to you alone.

644
00:41:49,890 --> 00:41:52,000
What did he mean?

645
00:42:10,780 --> 00:42:12,390
Huh?

646
00:42:21,470 --> 00:42:24,880
Yamamoto, regarding what you just said...

647
00:42:56,620 --> 00:42:58,100
Eh?

648
00:43:41,270 --> 00:43:45,040
Welcome, Yamamoto.

649
00:43:51,950 --> 00:43:56,370
[I won't be back for a while.]

650
00:44:00,310 --> 00:44:04,120
[Next Episode]
I didn't expect you to come so soon.

651
00:44:04,120 --> 00:44:08,950
After seeing your message, there's no way I can calm down.

652
00:44:10,220 --> 00:44:11,960
I mean, you...

653
00:44:14,380 --> 00:44:16,090
You asked me to...
